00:47:07.110 --> 00:47:09.960
And no, he was not
going to divorce himself

00:47:09.960 --> 00:47:11.681
from the Democratic Party.

00:47:11.681 --> 00:47:12.543
AUDIENCE: But what if
it's not a president?

00:47:12.543 --> 00:47:14.270
What if it's somebody
else in that situation?

00:47:14.270 --> 00:47:15.645
AL FRANKEN: Well,
people do that.

00:47:15.645 --> 00:47:18.900
I mean, Bernie Sanders is not a
member of the Democratic Party.

00:47:18.900 --> 00:47:21.090
So people are free to do that.

00:47:21.090 --> 00:47:22.200
And people do that.

00:47:22.200 --> 00:47:23.730
But I'm a Democrat.

00:47:23.730 --> 00:47:25.440
I'm a Democrat, because--

00:47:25.440 --> 00:47:28.640
and I start the book
about why I'm a Democrat.

00:47:28.640 --> 00:47:30.750
And I'm a Democrat.

00:47:30.750 --> 00:47:35.040
I grew up in St.
Louis Park, Minnesota.

00:47:35.040 --> 00:47:37.260
My dad didn't
graduate high school.

00:47:37.260 --> 00:47:38.700
He was a printing salesman.

00:47:38.700 --> 00:47:41.164
I grew up in a two-bedroom,
one-bath house.

00:47:41.164 --> 00:47:43.080
But I felt like the
luckiest kid in the world,

00:47:43.080 --> 00:47:45.540
because I was growing
up middle class,

00:47:45.540 --> 00:47:51.900
at the height of the middle
class, in the '50s in America

00:47:51.900 --> 00:47:54.360
in Minnesota in St.
Louis Park, and I

00:47:54.360 --> 00:47:57.700
felt like I could do
anything I wanted.

00:47:57.700 --> 00:48:02.700
And I don't feel like kids
feel that way today, maybe.

00:48:02.700 --> 00:48:05.450
But when I went to
college, I met my wife.

00:48:05.450 --> 00:48:07.200
And she didn't grow up that way.

00:48:07.200 --> 00:48:10.660
Her father died when
she was 18 months old.

00:48:10.660 --> 00:48:11.740
She had a younger sister.

00:48:11.740 --> 00:48:16.650
Her mom was widowed at
age 29 with five kids.

00:48:16.650 --> 00:48:19.410
And they made it because
of Social Security survivor

00:48:19.410 --> 00:48:21.240
benefits.

00:48:21.240 --> 00:48:24.120
Sometimes they didn't
have enough to eat.

00:48:24.120 --> 00:48:25.320
A lot of times.

00:48:25.320 --> 00:48:27.720
Sometimes the heat
was turned off.

00:48:27.720 --> 00:48:29.760
And this is in Portland, Maine.

00:48:29.760 --> 00:48:32.370
Sometimes the phone
was turned off.

00:48:32.370 --> 00:48:33.180
But they made it.

00:48:33.180 --> 00:48:35.270
And all the girls
went to college

00:48:35.270 --> 00:48:39.090
on combinations of Pell
grants, which at that time

00:48:39.090 --> 00:48:43.470
paid for about 80% of a
public college education,

00:48:43.470 --> 00:48:45.780
and scholarships.

00:48:45.780 --> 00:48:49.650
And my mother-in-law ended
up going to college when

00:48:49.650 --> 00:48:50.910
the youngest--

00:48:50.910 --> 00:48:53.960
there was one younger my wife.

00:48:53.960 --> 00:48:57.050
When the youngest went to high
school, she got a GI loan.

00:48:57.050 --> 00:49:00.720
Her husband fought
in World War II.

00:49:00.720 --> 00:49:04.350
And that allowed her
to go to college.

00:49:04.350 --> 00:49:05.850
She ended up being a teacher.

00:49:05.850 --> 00:49:07.845
She taught Title
I kids, poor kids,

00:49:07.845 --> 00:49:10.950
so all her loans were forgiven.

00:49:10.950 --> 00:49:13.200
They tell you in this
country to pull yourself up

00:49:13.200 --> 00:49:15.690
by the bootstraps.

00:49:15.690 --> 00:49:17.070
I think we all believe that.

00:49:17.070 --> 00:49:20.050
But first, you have
to have the boots.

00:49:20.050 --> 00:49:27.360
And the federal government
gave Franni's family the boots.

00:49:27.360 --> 00:49:28.950
And that's what we believe. in.

00:49:28.950 --> 00:49:33.200
We believe in creating
opportunity for everybody.

00:49:33.200 --> 00:49:35.930
And I think that
this president--

00:49:35.930 --> 00:49:40.950
witness his budget, witness
his health care legislation--

00:49:40.950 --> 00:49:43.770
doesn't believe that.

00:49:43.770 --> 00:49:47.322
And that's why I'm a Democrat.

00:49:47.322 --> 00:49:47.822
Yes?

00:49:47.822 --> 00:49:51.678
[APPLAUSE]

